            <section class="project-content">

                <div class="project-description">

                    <h2>About This Project</h2>
                    <p>This project was made in the context of a branding class with the objective of re-imagining a poster of a film of choice. My choice was Hacksaw Ridge, by Mel Gibson, and we were given creative freedom to re-imagine the poster with any methodology i wanted. I decided to challange myself and do something I wasn't comfortable with and went with illustration.</b></p>
                    <p>Hacksaw Ridge is a 2016 biographical war film directed by Mel Gibson and written by Andrew Knight and Robert Schenkkan, based on the 2004 documentary The Conscientious Objector directed by Terry Benedict.</p>
                    <p>The film focuses on the World War II experiences of Desmond Doss, an American pacifist combat medic who, as a Seventh-day Adventist Christian, refused to carry or use a weapon or firearm of any kind.</p>
                    
                </div>

